<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Need some help with Game Music Emu]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10102&amp;p=112249#p112249"><![CDATA[
Since I don't think I'm skillful enough to mess with emulator code, I settled for checking all the as3/alchemy compilation mess. I'm not really sure, but I believe that all instances of the gme library create static emulators (in flash at least). Anyway, I solved my problem in a very simple way: linking two different swc of gme to my project. Now it works wonderfully. Is not a good solution, since it requires recompiling gme with alchemy into two different swc libraries that work in exactly the same way, but are in different packages, and it takes more space on the final swf than it should (but can be reduced by using just the nsf part of gme). I'll keep trying to find a better solution. Thx for all your answers.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=5996">Ikki666</a> — Fri May 17, 2013 11:30 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
