<id>http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10102&amp;p=112198#p112198</id>
<link href="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10102&amp;p=112198#p112198"/>
<title type="html"><![CDATA[Re: Need some help with Game Music Emu]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=10102&amp;p=112198#p112198"><![CDATA[
GME plays NSF files, which only support one track playing at a time. You'd need to run two instances of GME if you want sound effects at the same time. Though, I didn't do the swf porting, so maybe the author did something to help with sound effects (I vaguely remember an email about this issue, but can't find it offhand in my mailbox).<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=17">blargg</a> — Thu May 16, 2013 10:15 am</p><hr />
]]></content>
